      • setUseParentHandlers

        public void setUseParentHandlers(boolean useParentHandlers)
        Specify whether this logger should send its output to its parent Logger. This means that any LogRecords will also be written to the parent's Handlers, and potentially to its parent, recursively up the namespace.
        Parameters:
        useParentHandlers - true if output is to be sent to the logger's parent.
        Throws:
        SecurityException - if a security manager exists, this logger is not anonymous, and the caller does not have LoggingPermission("control").
